<h2 id="5-fixing-the-notfoundexception-error">5. Fixing the NotFoundException (error)</h2>

<p>Yes, even if the code is correct, this error might appear:<br />
<em>‚ÄúCould not load file or assembly ‚Äòprojectnamehere, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null‚Äô or one of its dependencies. The system cannot find the file specified.‚Äù</em></p>

<p>This is caused by <strong>ASP.NET Runtime</strong> - but it can be easily solved by creating a directory named <strong>bin</strong> and copying the executable there.</p>

<p>If you have your executable in the Debug folder:<br />
<em>‚Äúproject_name/bin/Debug/asp_server.exe‚Äù</em> &lt;- original path</p>

<p>You have to create the <strong>Bin</strong> folder here (you‚Äôll also have to copy the application in the new directory):<br />
<em>‚Äúproject_name/bin/Debug/<strong>bin</strong>/asp_server.exe‚Äù</em> &lt;- new path</p>

<p>Now you can safely run your ASP.NET server, from the default location (not from the bin folder).</p>

<p>Note: if you change anything in the server‚Äôs source and recompile it, you have to do the copy-paste thing again.</p>

<p><strong><em>Later Edit:</em></strong> there seems to be a problem with the extensions - the server is only serving .aspx files (apparently files with other extensions can not be ‚Äúseen‚Äù). Don‚Äôt know sure what can cause this‚Ä¶</p>
